<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Official Raid Schedule:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  <br>
Official raid times are as follows:<br>
Monday-Thursday: 7pm EST - 11pm EST (Can start as early as 6pm EST and/or end as late as 12am EST)<br>
Friday: 7pm EST - 11pm EST (Can start as early as 6pm EST and/or end as late as 2am EST)<br>
Saturday: 2pm EST - 3am EST<br>
In the event where a scheduled or surprise patch results in respawns occurring on an off day, the off  day(s) will be rescheduled to a later date.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Attendance:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Attending official guild raids is mandatory for all members, probationary members and applicants -  XP'ing, playing twinks, attending other raids, or otherwise not attending official guild raids when you are online and there is an official raid in progress is unacceptable.  Logging out prior to and back on after a raid is monitored and disciplinary action will be taken, subject to discussions with guild officers.<br>
<br>
Should you be required to leave a raid in progress, you must inform the Raid Leader or an officer, and announce your departure in the /gu and /raid channels.<br>
<br>
If you are unable to attend raids for whatever reason, you MUST inform the leadership via the Will You Be There forum.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Conduct:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
All raid participants are expected to be on time for raids however the Leadership is aware that not everyone can be on time, every day due to real life concerns.  Should you find that your schedule does not mesh with the Official Raid Schedule (in the short and long term) you must ensure that the Leadership is aware of any scheduling conflicts.<br>
<br>
All raid participants are expected to listen to and follow all instructions given during a raid.  Instructions are typically given by the Raid Leader, guild officers, and other designated persons (i.e. cleric and tank commanders).<br>
<br>
All raid participants are expected to conduct themselves in an appropriate manner disruptive behaviour directed at the guild or the public is not acceptable.<br>
<br>
All raid participants are responsible for managing their user interface and game settings to minimize latency, chat spam, and other factors that affect their gameplay.  Some problems can be adressed <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub147.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showMessage?topicID=547.topic" target="top"><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">here.</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
All raid participants must ensure that all applicable channels are clear and easily readable during the course of a raid - /g, /gu, /raid and any other designated channel (i.e. /heal channel and /tank channel).  In the unfortunate instance where you have a particular person on ignore, you must ensure that the person is off ignore during the raid to ensure clear communication.  Instances where the failure to comply with these channel/communication requirements results in disruption of the raid, you will be penalized as per the discretion of the Leadership.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Assist and Main Assist:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
The Main Assist(s) will be clearly designated at the onset of a raid and/or encounter.  All raid participants are responsible for making the appropriate hotkeys required to facilitate their role in the raid (i.e. /assist [designated tank]).  If you don't know who the MA is, ask.<br>
<br>
All raid participants must ensure that they are assisting on the correct target prior to initiating any activity that will induce aggro, break mezmerizations, roots or other forms of crowd control.  There are NO exceptions to this and repeated instances of not assisting on the appropriate target will be penalized as per the discretion of the Leadership.<br>
<br>
All raid participants are expected to utilize an /assist key, where doing so is appropriate for their function in the raid (i.e. healers to aid in assist healing off of mobs that change aggro).<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Attendance System:</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Fire and Fury uses an honor system to keep track of attendance.  You will learn more of this once you have been admitted into our halls.  It's importance in loot distribution is described within the guild Loot Policy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/frage81292frm2.showNextMessage?topicID=26.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/frage81292frm2.emailToFriend?topicID=26.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/frage81292frm2.threadControl?topicID=26.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/rust/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/frage81292frm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/frage81292frm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="rage81292frm22">What we do<option value="rage81292frm1">General Discussion<option value="rage81292frm2">Guild Rules<option value="rage81292frm3">Applications<option value